<Content>Not the Bellagio, but just perfect for us !!! Ok it's old, ok the bedrooms don't look great, the remote was not working, and the sink was not great. BUT ! For the four of us, 23 to 28 year old, the bedroom was huge with a seperation between the 2 beds, fridge and microwave a nice bonus, parking with camera and someone all night long (much better than a new bedroom for us) the lady at the entrance simply outstanding : knowledeable nice and efficient, the airport shuttle free, and every hour, a bus stop across the street, the swimming pool is definitely nice, located between a M fast food and a sport bar, everybody was happy, and we had the best price of all Miami through Orbits, with no surprise when checkin (no resort fee, or additional person, parking just 2.4$). The hotel is not new, but the housekeepers do a good job (except they woke me up every morning...). After all that we read we were scared but it was so much what we needed that we stayed our 3 last nights. Not a super nice resort to spend your vacation, but perfect to spend a couple of days waiting for your planes. 
