<Content>Don't Book this Hotel--YOU WILL REGRET IT Do not book with this hotel. Especially for group bookings. I did a group booking for a pre-cruise one-night stay with this hotel in 10/07 for a reservation in 4/08. Additional reservations couldn't be made because of problems with their website and hotel staff stating their was no reservation to add on to. Their website was non-functional for 2 weeks and for an additional 4 weeks the manager of the hotel was never available to receive phone calls and never returned any calls. Requests for cancellations resulted in being told that a reservation couldn't be cancelled if it doesn't exist. An in-person visit to this run-down hotel didn't resolve the problem (and of course, the manager wasn't there again). 10 days before the cruise, and 10 days before the day that was booked (if we were going to stay there), this hotel without authorization charged my card for the 10 rooms, This is dispite the fact that no credit card authorization form had been signed, a request to cancel the reservation had been stated in 11/07 and 12/07 (well before the 24-hour cancellation period, and that the staff repeatedly stated over a 6 month period that no reservation existed. So, if you want problems that cost you more than one-night than book here but if you do, based on my experience you will regret it. Please note that although my review may state that I stayed there, I actually did not but had to fill in the hotel stay section that couldn't be left blank because it is an area that you are required to fill in to post your reviews. 
