<Author>yo_bman
<Content>AWFUL -- Definition of a SLUM! This place is the definition of AWFUL. We booked it in total desperation and sight unseen due to a missed connecting flight during spring break. I'm embarrassed to say we paid the same rate here as we did at the Four Seasons a few weeks earlier ($385 + tax). No we're not Four Seasons snobs, it was a special occasion for one night in L.A.Rooms at Airway Inn and Suites are truly the most disgusting any of us had ever seen. We're talking gum on the wall, cracked ceilings, and moldy tubs. We laid the airline blankets down on top of the bed (thank God we kept them). Urine smells reek throughout the hallways. Truly a SLUM! When we went down to complain about the room conditions and rates, of course the manager just happened to leave town for the week. Amazing -- he was there when we checked in 10 minutes earlier. Since they don't post their rates anywhere on the web or in writing, we called back to check rates for the following weekend out of curiosity -- same room we paid $385 for was now $87. They totally took advantage of a plane full of us who missed our connections due to airline mistakes. Had we seen the place before booking, I would have paid $87 to rent a car, drive as far away from it as possible, and sleep in a parking lot!The only saving grace is that we got there after midnight and had a 6 am flight. Anything longer would have been too much to handle. SLEEP IN THE AIRPORT OR RENT AN R.V. BEFORE EVEN CONSIDERING AIRWAY INN AND SUITES! Horrible, horrible, horrible! 
