<Content>Lower End Hotel I stayed here because I was coming in late in the evening and had to catch an early morning flight. I didn't want to spend $100 plus for a room that I was going to be in for less than 8 hours.This place is right on NW 36th across from the airport. I had a corner room right on the street but with the windows closed, it was not that noisy. The room was pretty nice and very clean. The TV worked and there was a microwave and fridge. The bathroom was OK but there was no place to put your toilet kit. The shower worked well the night I arrived but the next morning, I could not get any hot water and I let the water run the whole time I was shaving.The hotel itself looks like an old dormitory and has an institutuion feel to it. It might be very depressing for many travelers. It seems that this place is frequented by patrons on the lower end of the economic spectrum. Although clean, there were some peanut shells on the floor of my stairway that were never cleaned up during my stay. There is a nice pool just off the loby in a courtyard. This might be nice on a warm afternoon or evening.I booked the hotel online for $59 for a single. With taxes and a mandatory safe fee of $1.75 and a parking fee of $2, the room came to $70 for the night. The restaurant at the hotel is closed but there is a McDonalds next door.One word of caution not releated to the hotel. I found it very difficult to find the car rental returns off of Le Jeune Road due to a lot of construction going on near the airport. I recommend calling your rental agency and getting detailed directions to their location from the hotel if you stay here. 
