<Content>Do not stay here Just stayed at the Airways Hotel last night (4/10/04). It reminded me of one of those dirty motels that are always on COPS. The place smelled like urine, the rooms were dirty, and it was all-around crappy. The people were rude at the desk, and could hardly speak english. At the end of a long, smelly hallway was our equally smelly and dirty room. The bed sheets were itchy and dirty-looking, and there were only 2 towels for a suite. There was a divider in between the beds, and there was only one TV for both sides. The wires on it were exposed, with no wall plate covering it (not to code). Late at night, someone was jiggling our door handle, so we placed our baggage in front ouf the door. We had to wake up early for a flight(5 AM), and the free shuttle to the airport was a joke. When the van showed up, the driver was drunk. He stumbled from the van, opened the back door, and went into the hotel lobby bathroom. We had to load our own bags, and it took him at least ten minutes to return. We arrived, luckily, on time, and unloaded our own bags on the airport curb. Although the brand name hotels charge more, stay at them. Pay for the safe shuttle and a good night's rest. THE AIRWAYS IS GARBAGE. DO NOT BOOK THERE! 
